<p class="">I said originally that I did not think that the Amendment was of any substance and I hoped, therefore, that the House would accept it. [HON. MEMBERS: "Why?"] The reason we accept it is that it fixes the number to start with at 10 and we think that a good thing, in view of the work which we know the Authority will have to do in the early stages. I do not know why hon. Gentlemen opposite should object to reference to Parliament. I should have thought they would haveâ€”[HON. MEMBERS: "It means nothing."] It means something. It means that the proposal has to be laid before Parliament.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
