<p class="">The hon. and learned Gentleman is a lawyer; I am not, but surely I am right in thinking that it is the case that a court cannot require the internal documents of a Government Department to be produced on a matter of this kind? If a Minister, presumably the Secretary of State, certified that he had been consulted, would that not be accepted as conclusive evidence?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-29870618-69a3-4f62-9b5b-ed19c4857882" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
